                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Certainly we all have our own tecniques and talents in this field.
<br />

<br />
My own...I started playing very early (as an enchanter) and pre Kunark experemented with charm extensively.
<br />

<br />
Early levels the Karanas we good
<br />

<br />
Mid level (30ish) I charmed in Kedge (zin fish had low mr)
<br />
Soon to specters.......etc
<br />

<br />
Now PoP (and general)
<br />

<br />
First thing i did when learning an area...scout out....spend time watching where wanderers are, statics, escape routes etc.
<br />

<br />
This said i will give an example of an area that is now easy for me...but i did leave a number of corpses to get there...
<br />

<br />
Tactics...upper area...Diaku
<br />

<br />
I scout out and notice the placement of all Sentry, Guardian and Scouts (my prefered pets in that order), then determine the best route to clear...Killing first potential adds to any fights (wanders or statics in my general area). My kill order is dependent on what is there....for example i seldom kill the other sentry that are up as they will be my next pet, or I wont attack a Sk if my pet is to low health.
<br />
Generaly even before the attack i have planned my next victem.
<br />
Learn agro radius, learn pathing...observe....
<br />

<br />
Now....I always duel wield and haste pet. I mostly slow enemy, I seldom root enemy, unless I want to have it do a bit more damage (diaku run at 20%). I almost never engage unless my pet is over 20% (unless a warrior, sentry or guardian.....and here i would then root and slow before sending in pet...where usualy I pull with tash as I send in pet).
<br />

<br />
I seldom do this with outside buffs, the diaku are just slow enough that with run 3 you can gain distance. Charm breaks.....sometimes root, sometimes mez, sometimes recharm direct, sometimes run.....(know where a safe zone out is...eg if you are always levitated you can run and drop into the se corner of the tactics pit and get away easy)
<br />

<br />
I generaly break charm with dispell.
<br />

<br />
I do have good equipment and aa......and when i solo upper tactics i am able to clear all there as well as all the way down the stairs and into the next room (i get this far by second or third clear).
<br />

<br />
Spell line up (tactics)
<br />

<br />
Tash
<br />
mezz
<br />
charm
<br />
root
<br />
slow
<br />
nuke
<br />
rune
<br />
variable (buff, dispell, invisi, dot)
<br />

<br />
In say 4 hours......3-6 aa gained (depends on if i am chatting or doing favours for guildies while doing this), about 1k in vender loot and between 0 and 3 highly polished gems(inclusive).
<br />

<br />
Now if you are fast, and able to get rid of pet, and tactics empty, you can also catch more than 1/2 of the stampeeds by jumping down to the north west hall...you have near 1 min to react after hearing the pounding of hooves.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Galanteer
<br />
Mith Marr</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
