                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">However, regardless of what you do for charming, do not <span style="font-weight: bold">rely</span> on buffs you cannot cast yourself.  I can't stress the importance of this.  They're nice to have, yes.  However, don't depend on them to the point where you won't charm without them.  You need to get used to your actual self-buffed hit points so that if something goes FUBAR, you will be used to being able to deal with it with minimal pain to you.  That way when you DO get buffs, the extra cushion of HP it will give you will mean that you can suffer through more screw ups, which means less dying overall.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sleeping for 65 nights (with 167 interruptions...)
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=467231" target="_blank" class="postlink">ZZZzzzzzz...</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
