                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If using a pet to kill a named (i.e. BoT elementals), I will always slow my pet and keep it slowed until we get to the named.  I invis to break charm, re-Tash, and then recharm.  They I cast haste to overwrite the charm (I use Anya's Quickening for charmed pets).  That way I have a fresh new charm (which again can break at anytime) for the named.  I haven't had a charmed pet break on a named once using this method, but then again I only use it in groups.
<br />

<br />
I always stay in the corner if possible when using charmed pet because it it gets loose, I have a better chance to channel Word of Morrel.  WoM - CoD has always worked for me.  Don't try to take on summoning mobs with Charmed pet (i.e. Militis, not good at all) or you will die 75% of the time on a charm break.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
