                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">BoT wasp CY is where I usually solo.  There are two types of wasps...cleric and warrior.  I usually start off in SE corner.  Spell line-up during normal soloing is:
<br />

<br />
Arcane Rune
<br />
Howl of Tashania
<br />
Pacification
<br />
CoD
<br />
Nuke
<br />
Forlorn Deeds
<br />
Scryer's Tresspass
<br />
Greater Fetter
<br />

<br />
I start off with NDT up...I will root, tash, charm, shissar, and NDT the warrior wasp near the pot that ports you close to the exit of BoT (not the tower).  Then I unmem NDT and go to my normal lineup above.
<br />

<br />
When root breaks, I send him to the cleric wasp at the tree.  As long as pet gets first couple of hits in, you can slow+throw in a single nuke and the wasp generally won't get aggro on you.  This works for all wasps.  If charm breaks, you have two choices...if you have an ER4 item and sow (perm illusion axp ability is awesome...druid doggie form lasts for like 10 hours and thru zoning)...run just out of range and recharm pet.  If you don't have these items, you can just run to the left pot and tp to the entrance of BoT...you instantly lose aggro on everything...you still have to zone out, tho.  If you don't, all previously-aggro wasps will immediately come running for you when you enter the wasp CY again.
<br />

<br />
Main thing to remember is never try to re-charm when a hasted pet is within melee range =)
<br />

<br />
As far 65th level normal LDoN adventures...I never run without a CoD pet with haste+two weapons.  Just keep WoM/Color Cloud up at all times.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
